29/05/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Warplanes shelled suspected positions of the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) in northern Iraq on Thursday (May 28th), the general staff said in a statement on its website. The operation came after a landmine killed six Turkish soldiers and injured another 11.
In other news, at least one person died and nine were injured when a hot air balloon carrying tourists plunged from the sky in the central region of Cappadocia, local media reported on Friday. Witnesses say one balloon crashed into another just after lifting off, at an altitude of 200m. (Hurriyet, Zaman, Hurriyet, RIA-Novosti, BBC - 29/05/09; Reuters - 28/05/09)
